                  <msContents>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Hamilton_41-part1-item1" n="1">
                        <locus>(fols. 2r-195r)</locus>
                        <title key="work_14611">Sermones quadragesimales</title>
                        <rubric><add>Opus quadragesimale</add></rubric>
                        <note>The first three and last three incipits as follows:</note>
                        <msItem><rubric>Quarta feria cinerum sermo</rubric>
                        <incipit><quote>Videntes admirati sunt <gap reason="editorial"/></quote> Ciues obsesse ciuitatis et vallati forti et grandi inimicorum exercitu </incipit></msItem>
                        <msItem>
                           <incipit><locus>(fol. 5v)</locus> <quote>Puer meus iacet paralaticus <gap reason="editorial"></gap></quote> Inter alia egritudini curandi utilia sunt duo precipue, primum est ut eger se curandum committat medico de quo confidat</incipit>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem>
                           <incipit><locus>(fol. 9r)</locus> <quote>Ego autem dico vobis <gap reason="editorial"></gap></quote> In eodem foro seu mercato in <sic>mundinibus</sic> consueuerunt vendi viles merces et preciose</incipit>
                        </msItem>
                        
                        <msItem>
                           <incipit><locus>(fol. 169r)</locus> <quote>Sciens iesus quia ut uenit hora <gap reason="editorial"></gap></quote> Prudens dux peregrinorum debens eos ducere per v<supplied reason="omitted">i</supplied>am asperam prouidet eis quibus sustentari possint</incipit>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem><!-- 351 -->
                           <incipit><locus>(fol. 172r)</locus> <quote>Nolite me vocare <gap reason="editorial"></gap></quote> In eodem libro legimus predictam mulierem esse pulchram valde</incipit><!-- bordeaux f. 66rb; image 74 -->
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem><!-- 386 -->
                           <incipit><locus>(fol. 189v)</locus> <quote>Quo abiit abiit dilectus <gap reason="editorial"></gap></quote> Non est reliquenda hodie sic sauciata doloribus super ploratu filii</incipit>
                        
                        <explicit>Ploratus simus tue resurrectionis consortes in secula seculorum. Amen.</explicit></msItem>
                        
                        <finalRubric>Expliciunt postille quadragesimales</finalRubric>
                        <note>Apparently the same collection as <bibl type="ms" subtype="external">Bordeaux, BM 294</bibl> fols. 1-81v but lacking the two final sermons in that manuscript. Cf. <bibl subtype="external" type="ms">Darmstadt, Universitäts- und Landesbibliothek Darmstadt, Hs 2207</bibl> fols. 2r–86v. Followed by three additional sermons:</note>
                        <!--
                           sermo 2: puer meus iacet
                           sermo 3: ego autem dico
                           sermo 4: cum sero esset 
                           
                           last sermons: 
                           Quo abiit abiit [seems to end as Bordeaux fol 75ra]
                           
                           
                           followed by two more:
                           Tu autem domine
                           Ecce salvator
                           
                           cf. Darmstadt, Universitäts- und Landesbibliothek Darmstadt - Hs 2207 2ra – 86va 
                           and Bordeaux, Bib. mun. 294, fols. 1-81v
                           online at https://bvmm.irht.cnrs.fr/consult/consult.php?reproductionId=3726 
                        (the first four sermons match -->
                       
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 195r-197r)</locus>
                        <incipit><quote><supplied>P</supplied>osui faciem meam ut petram <gap reason="editorial"/></quote> Frequenter contigit quod bona alicui exhibita causant ei molestiam</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 197r-198v)</locus>
                        <incipit><quote><supplied>T</supplied>u autem domine sabaoth <gap reason="editorial"/></quote> Nota quod iustum iudicium dei timendum est propter tria, primo iram inflexibilem</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 198v-200r; 200v blank)</locus>
                        <incipit><quote><supplied>E</supplied>cce saluator tuus venit tibi <gap reason="editorial"/></quote> Non otiosis sed operantibus redditur merces eterna Sapien. 10. Redit iustis mercedem laborum suorum. Nota merces recipitur sceleriter persoluitur liberaliter.</incipit>
                     </msItem>
