                  <msContents>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fol. 201v; 201r blank)</locus>
                        <incipit><quote>Memento homo quia cinis es etc.</quote> Per cinerem significatur penitentia propter tres causas siue virtutes quas in cinere euidenter videmus</incipit>
                        <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Hamilton_41-part2-item1" n="1">
                        <locus>(fols. 202r-262v)</locus>
                        <title key="work_14611">Sermones quadgragesimales</title>
                        <rubric>Item sermones quadgragesimales</rubric>
                        <note>Incipits of the first three and last three sermons as follows:</note>
                        <msItem><incipit><quote>Sedit in cinere et spersit cinerem <gap reason="editorial"/></quote> Hodie fratres karissimi incipit tempus decime quo unusquisque debet domino suo et hoc de toto corpore suo</incipit></msItem>
                        <msItem>
                           <!-- 413 -->
                           <incipit><locus>(fol. 203r)</locus> <quote>Accessit centurio rogans <gap reason="editorial"/></quote> Tota intencio ecclesie fratres karissimi in ista quadragesima est ut peccatores ad penitenciam reducant</incipit>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem>
                           <incipit><locus>(fol. 204r)</locus> <quote>Quare ieiunauinmus <gap reason="editorial"/></quote> In prenotatis verbis fratres karissimi duo notare debemus, de quibus Ysay propheta domini interrogauit</incipit>
                        </msItem>
                        
                        <!--  518? -->
                     <!--   <msItem>
                           <incipit><locus>(fol. 255v)</locus> <quote>Traditus est ad mortem <gap reason="editorial"/></quote> Hodie fratres karissimi celebratur saluatoris nostri tradicio quia in hac hie ut dicit Luc</incipit>
                        </msItem>-->
                        <msItem>
                           <incipit><locus>(fol. 257r)</locus> <quote>Comedite amici mei <gap reason="editorial"/></quote> Karissimi, scribit Salomon ista uerba in Cantica canticorum et tanguntur duo verba in eis</incipit>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem>
                           <incipit><locus>(fol. 258v)</locus> Hodie fratres karissimi campane non pulsantur, missarum solempnia debito more non teneantur</incipit>
                        </msItem>
                        
                        <msItem>
                           <incipit><locus>(fol. 262r)</locus> <quote>O vos omnes qui transitis <gap reason="editorial"/></quote> Verba predicta fratres karissimi scripsit Ier. in libro lac. lamentacionum quod ipse exposuit et exclamauit vehementissime</incipit>
                           <explicit defective="true">De quo Job xxo ait, Quousque confligitis animam meam et atteritis</explicit>
                        </msItem>
                        <note>Apparently the same collection as in BSB Clm 18313, fols. 2-18 and Gotha Chart A 24c fols. 129ra-166ra (see E. Wunderle, <title>Katalog der mittelalterlichen lateinischen Papierhandschriften</title> (2002) 83-4), here imperfect at the end due to loss of leaves.</note>
                        <!-- ends imperect? cf. ; and Gotha, Chart A 24c  -->
                        <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Hamilton_41-part2-item2" n="2">
                        <locus>(fol. 263r-265v)</locus>
                        <title type="desc" key="work_14583">Sermon on the Visitation of the Virgin Mary</title>
                        <rubric>Sermo de visitacione marie matris domini nostri iesu christi</rubric>
                        <incipit><quote>Exurgens Maria <gap reason="editorial"/></quote> Postquam Maria suum sensum apperuit quam angelus in persona tocius trinitatis expectauit, ymmo tocius genus humanum et angelus, reuertebatur ad domum</incipit>
                        <explicit>quia ipsa concussit capud antiqui serpentis et conpletum est id in ea quod dicitur Genes. 3, Ipsa conteret caput serpentis et cetera</explicit>
                        <note>Followed by a later note on the seven 'peccata aliena' and seven metals.</note>
                        <textLang mainLang="la" >Latin</textLang>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <colophon>Deo gracias etc. Hilf God Maria berad</colophon><textLang mainLang="la" otherLangs="de">Latin, German</textLang>
                     </msItem>
